{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NqYA35FUfkoYAvBUygtQDL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# patches/ — BMAD Workflow Enforcement Patches\n     2→\n     3→## Purpose\n     4→\n     5→Markdown patch files applied to BMAD workflow targets during `codeharness init`.\n     6→Each patch encodes operational learnings (FR33) as enforcement rules that\n     7→prevent recurrence of observed failures.\n     8→\n     9→## Directory Structure (FR35)\n    10→\n    11→```\n    12→patches/\n    13→  dev/enforcement.md        — Dev agent guardrails\n    14→  review/enforcement.md     — Review gates (proof quality, coverage)\n    15→  verify/story-verification.md — Black-box proof requirements\n    16→  sprint/planning.md        — Sprint planning pre-checks\n    17→  retro/enforcement.md      — Retrospective quality metrics\n    18→```\n    19→\n    20→Subdirectories map to BMAD workflow roles (or analysis categories like `observability/`).\n    21→\n    22→## Observability Module (`observability/`)\n    23→\n    24→Semgrep YAML rules for static analysis of observability gaps. Each `.yaml` file is a standalone Semgrep config — no build step required. Deleting a rule file removes that check.\n    25→\n    26→**Rules:**\n    27→- `catch-without-logging.yaml` — Detects catch blocks without error/warn logging (WARNING)\n    28→- `function-no-debug-log.yaml` — Detects functions without debug/info logging (INFO)\n    29→- `error-path-no-log.yaml` — Detects error paths (throw/return err) without preceding log (WARNING)\n    30→\n    31→**Test fixtures** (`.ts` files alongside rules, annotated with `// ruleid:` / `// ok:` comments):\n    32→- `catch-without-logging.ts` — Test cases for catch-without-logging rule\n    33→- `function-no-debug-log.ts` — Test cases for function-no-debug-log rule\n    34→- `error-path-no-log.ts` — Test cases for error-path-no-log rule\n    35→\n    36→**Testing:** `semgrep --test patches/observability/` runs annotated test fixtures.\n    37→\n    38→**Customization:** Edit YAML rules to add custom logger patterns (e.g., `logger.error(...)` for winston). Rules use `pattern-not` / `pattern-not-inside` to detect absence of logging.\n    39→\n    40→## How Patches Work\n    41→\n    42→1. `src/templates/bmad-patches.ts` reads files via `readPatchFile(role, name)`\n    43→2. `src/lib/bmad.ts` maps patch names to BMAD workflow target files via `PATCH_TARGETS`\n    44→3. `src/lib/patch-engine.ts` injects patch content between `CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START/END` markers\n    45→4. `src/commands/teardown.ts` removes patches on teardown\n    46→\n    47→## Editing Patches\n    48→\n    49→- Edit `.md` files directly — no TypeScript rebuild required (runtime `readFileSync`)\n    50→- Each patch MUST have a `## WHY` section explaining the operational failure it prevents (FR36)\n    51→- Do NOT change filenames without updating `readPatchFile()` calls in `bmad-patches.ts`\n    52→- Do NOT remove inline fallback strings in `bmad-patches.ts` — they cover npm installs without `patches/`\n    53→\n    54→## Adding a New Patch\n    55→\n    56→1. Create `patches/{role}/{name}.md` with `## WHY` section\n    57→2. Add a template function in `src/templates/bmad-patches.ts` calling `readPatchFile(role, name)`\n    58→3. Add entry to `PATCH_TEMPLATES` in `bmad-patches.ts`\n    59→4. Add target mapping in `PATCH_TARGETS` in `src/lib/bmad.ts`\n    60→5. Add tests in `src/templates/__tests__/bmad-patches.test.ts`\n    61→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WFzjRFzKVwYJKtrGR84YZ3","session_id":"4b69c0d8-c2d9-426d-9413-456ae301bb7e","uuid":"4a00e4e5-dd66-4f68-a2db-6f44ae23c8c9","timestamp":"2026-03-28T13:40:21.361Z"}
