{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013CsZhbGoXJhUnjvd3GmyCi","type":"tool_result","content":"25:- **`environment-provable`** — Evidence comes from `docker exec` commands and observability queries. Full Docker verification environment required. Each AC section needs at least one `docker exec`, `docker ps/logs`, or observability query. Evidence must come from running the installed CLI/tool in Docker, not from grepping source.\n33:- `<!-- verification: environment-provable -->` — Requires full Docker environment with observability. Evidence: `docker exec` commands, VictoriaLogs queries, multi-service interaction.\n39:3. Do you need Docker, external services, or observability? → `environment-provable`\n42:**Do not over-tag.** Most stories are `test-provable` or `runtime-provable`. Only use `environment-provable` when Docker infrastructure is genuinely needed. Only use `escalate` as a last resort.\n46:After each `docker exec` command (applicable to `environment-provable` stories), query the observability backend for log events from the last 30 seconds."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WFzjRFzKVwYJKtrGR84YZ3","session_id":"4b69c0d8-c2d9-426d-9413-456ae301bb7e","uuid":"e7b4bdd8-4856-489c-a907-d3b93a93d151","timestamp":"2026-03-28T13:40:40.209Z"}
