{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WFzjRFzKVwYJKtrGR84YZ3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs.md\n**Git vs Story Discrepancies:** 0 (within original scope)\n**Issues Found:** 1 High, 4 Medium, 3 Low\n\n## CRITICAL ISSUES\nNone.\n\n## HIGH ISSUES (fixed)\n1. **`patches/retro/enforcement.md` contains legacy terms** — \"black-box verification\" (line 14) and \"integration-required\" (line 22-23). These enforcement docs are read by agents and directly contradict the four-tier vocabulary. **FIXED:** Replaced with tier-aware language.\n\n## MEDIUM ISSUES (fixed)\n2. **`patches/AGENTS.md` stale description** — line 15 described `story-verification.md` as \"Black-box proof requirements\" after the file was rewritten. **FIXED:** Updated to \"Tier-appropriate proof requirements\".\n3. **`extractSection` helper fragile** — Used `content.split()` which matches heading text anywhere in prose, not just as markdown headings. **FIXED:** Rewrote to use line-anchored `startsWith` matching.\n4. **Missing test for Task 4.3** — No test verified the Observability Evidence section mentions `environment-provable`. **FIXED:** Added test assertion.\n5. **`extractSection` exact-match breaking** — After line-anchored fix, headings like `#### \\`escalate\\` stories` didn't match `#### \\`escalate\\`` exactly. **FIXED:** Changed to `startsWith` matching.\n\n## LOW ISSUES (not fixed — documented below)\n\n**Review Complete.** Story status: `verifying` (already set). Issues fixed: 5 HIGH+MEDIUM. All 56 story-specific tests pass. Full suite: 321 tests, 0 failures. Coverage: 96.85% overall, all 158 files above 80%.\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `patches/retro/enforcement.md` used legacy terms \"black-box\" and \"integration-required\" — inconsistent with the four-tier vocabulary established by this story\n- MEDIUM: `patches/AGENTS.md` had stale \"Black-box\" description for story-verification.md\n- MEDIUM: `extractSection` test helper used naive `split()` that could match heading text in prose\n- MEDIUM: Missing test coverage for Observability Evidence section tier-awareness (Task 4.3)\n- MEDIUM: `extractSection` exact-match broke on headings with trailing text (e.g., `#### \\`escalate\\` stories`)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` uses \"black-box verifier\" throughout (lines 2, 14, 70, 86, 88) — out of scope for this story, belongs to a separate template cleanup story\n- `src/modules/sprint/feedback.ts` line 119 uses \"black-box verification\" — out of scope, runtime code not targeted by this doc-only story\n- `src/commands/__tests__/verify.test.ts` uses `verifiability: 'cli-verifiable'` in test fixtures — these are legacy field values testing backward compatibility in the parser, intentionally kept\n- `src/commands/AGENTS.md` line 130 describes \"black-box story verification\" — out of scope for this story\n- `patches/retro/enforcement.md` overall still uses verification-generic language that doesn't reference tier names explicitly in all bullet points\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. 96.85% overall, all files above 80%.\n- The test file only tests content presence via `toContain` — it does not validate structural correctness (e.g., that tier sections appear in the correct order, or that decision criteria tables are well-formed)\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The four-tier vocabulary is now consistent across the 4 target files + 2 additional files fixed, but legacy terms remain in `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`, `src/modules/sprint/feedback.ts`, and `src/commands/AGENTS.md` — these should be addressed in a follow-up story to complete the vocabulary migration across the entire codebase\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed in this session.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total to