→\n   164→| AC | Status | Evidence |\n   165→|----|--------|----------|\n   166→| AC1 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-parser.test.ts` lines 451-528: 14 classifyTier tests covering all four tiers |\n   167→| AC2 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-parser.test.ts` lines 414-428: all four new tier tag values tested |\n   168→| AC3 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-parser.test.ts` lines 398-440: cli-verifiable, integration-required, unit-testable, black-box backward compat |\n   169→| AC4 | IMPLEMENTED | `verification-tier.test.ts` line 42: maxTier pair returns runtime-provable |\n   170→| AC5 | IMPLEMENTED | `verification-tier.test.ts` line 33: maxTier([]) returns test-provable |\n   171→| AC6 | IMPLEMENTED | `verification-tier.test.ts` line 45: maxTier triple returns environment-provable |\n   172→| AC7 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-blackbox.test.ts` lines 481-585: all four tiers tested for Docker enforcement |\n   173→| AC8 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-blackbox.test.ts` lines 587-606: unit-testable backward compat skips Docker |\n   174→| AC9 | IMPLEMENTED | `validation-acs.test.ts` lines 152-200: getTestProvableACs + getCliVerifiableACs equivalence |\n   175→| AC10 | IMPLEMENTED | validation-runner.test.ts: all tests pass, no regressions |\n   176→| AC11 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-parser.test.ts` lines 106, 111, 229, 232, 253-259, 333-336, 357-360: tier field assertions |\n   177→| AC12 | IMPLEMENTED | 152 test files, 4015 tests, 0 failures |\n   178→\n   179→### Git vs Story Discrepancies\n   180→\n   181→None. Story claims zero code changes; git confirms no source files were modified.\n   182→\n   183→### Coverage\n   184→\n   185→- Overall: 96.86% (target: 90%) — PASS\n   186→- Per-file floor: all 158 files above 80% — PASS\n   187→\n   188→### Findings\n   189→\n   190→**LOW-1: classifyTier barrel re-export not tested through index.ts**\n   191→`classifyTier` is re-exported from `src/modules/verify/index.ts` (line 64) but `index.test.ts` mocks `parser.js` entirely and never verifies the `classifyTier` re-export works through the barrel. The `verification-tier.test.ts` tests barrel re-exports for `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `maxTier`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` (lines 141-147) but not `classifyTier`. This is LOW because `classifyTier` is thoroughly tested via direct import in `verify-parser.test.ts`.\n   192→\n   193→**LOW-2: Story line references in Dev Agent Record may drift**\n   194→The completion notes reference specific line numbers (e.g., \"lines 414-432\") which will become stale if test files are edited. This is a documentation fragility, not a code issue.\n   195→\n   196→**LOW-3: No negative-path test for classifyTier with conflicting runtime + test keywords**\n   197→Tests cover escalate > environment > runtime priority, but don't test runtime > test priority explicitly (e.g., a description with both \"function returns\" and \"CLI output\" keywords). Currently covered implicitly by the priority-order test at line 501-506, but a dedicated test would be clearer.\n   198→\n   199→## File List\n   200→\n   201→No files changed. This was an audit-only story.\n   202→\n   203→## Change Log\n   204→\n   205→- 2026-03-27: Audit completed — all test coverage confirmed present from stories 16-1 through 16-7. Zero code changes needed. Story marked for review.\n   206→- 2026-03-27: Adversarial code review completed — all 12 ACs verified IMPLEMENTED, 0 HIGH/MEDIUM issues, 3 LOW findings (tech debt). Coverage 96.86% overall, all files above 80%. Status set to verifying.\n   207→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FnD1p4BzuwR8M458ncZKjU","session_id":"4b69c0d8-c2d9-426d-9413-456ae301bb7e","uuid":"0c08e76c-3e7d-43dd-97c3-ac2f1b34783e","timestamp":"2026-03-28T13:59:12.673Z"}
