{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Shbhakhph4G8EhUztSCQSc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16-8: Update All Tests for Verification Tier Rework\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: verifying\n     5→\n     6→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     7→\n     8→## Story\n     9→\n    10→As a codeharness developer,\n    11→I want all tests to use the new `VerificationTier` vocabulary and cover the new functions,\n    12→So that `npm test` passes with zero regressions and the new tier system has full test coverage.\n    13→\n    14→## Acceptance Criteria\n    15→\n    16→- [x] AC1: Given `verify-parser.test.ts`, when `classifyTier` tests are inspected, then they cover all four tiers (`test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate`) with keyword-based classification <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [x] AC2: Given `verify-parser.test.ts`, when `parseVerificationTag` tests are inspected, then they cover all four new tier names (`test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate`) as valid tag values <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [x] AC3: Given `verify-parser.test.ts`, when backward compat tests are inspected, then `parseVerificationTag('<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->')` returns `'test-provable'` and `parseVerificationTag('<!-- verification: integration-required -->')` returns `'environment-provable'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→- [x] AC4: Given `verification-tier.test.ts`, when `maxTier(['test-provable', 'runtime-provable'])` is tested, then it returns `'runtime-provable'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→- [x] AC5: Given `verification-tier.test.ts`, when `maxTier([])` is tested, then it returns `'test-provable'` (default) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→- [x] AC6: Given `verification-tier.test.ts`, when `maxTier(['test-provable', 'environment-provable', 'runtime-provable'])` is tested, then it returns `'environment-provable'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→- [x] AC7: Given `verify-blackbox.test.ts`, when tier-based Docker enforcement tests are inspected, then they cover `**Tier:** test-provable`, `**Tier:** runtime-provable`, `**Tier:** environment-provable`, and `**Tier:** escalate` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→- [x] AC8: Given `verify-blackbox.test.ts`, when backward compat tier test is inspected, then `**Tier:** unit-testable` still results in Docker enforcement being skipped <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→- [x] AC9: Given `validation-acs.test.ts`, when inspected, then it tests both `getTestProvableACs()` (new name) and `getCliVerifiableACs()` (deprecated alias), confirming they return the same data <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→- [x] AC10: Given `validation-runner.test.ts`, when inspected, then all `verificationMethod` assertions still pass with no regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→- [x] AC11: Given `verify-parser.test.ts` `parseStoryACs` tests, when a story file with new tier tags is parsed, then each `ParsedAC` has the correct `tier` field <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→- [x] AC12: Given `npm test`, when run after all changes, then all tests pass with 0 failures <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    28→\n    29→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    30→\n    31→- [x] Task 1: Audit `verify-parser.test.ts` for classifyTier coverage (AC: 1)\n    32→  - [x] 1.1: Confirm `describe('classifyTier')` block has tests for each of the four tiers using keyword-based descriptions\n    33→  - [x] 1.2: Confirm priority-order test exists (escalate > environment > runtime > test)\n    34→  - [x] 1.3: Add any missing tier keyword tests if gaps found\n    35→- [x] Task 2: Audit `verify-parser.test.ts` for parseVerificationTag coverage (AC: 2, 3)\n    36→  - [x] 2.1: Confirm all four new tier names are tested as valid `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag values\n    37→  - [x] 2.2: Confirm backward compat tests exist for `cli-verifiable` → `test-provable` and `integration-required` → `environment-provable`\n    38→  - [x] 2.3: Add any missing backward compat tests (e.g., `unit-testable` → `test-provable`, `black-box` → `environment-provable`)\n    39→- [x] Task 3: Audit `verification-tier.test.ts` for maxTier coverage (AC: 4, 5, 6)\n    40→  - [x] 3.1: Confirm `maxTier([])` returns `test-provable`\n    41→  - [x] 3.2: Confirm `maxTier(['test-provable', 'runtime-provable'])` returns `runtime-provable`\n    42→  - [x] 3.3: Confirm `maxTier(['test-provable', 'environment-provable', 'runtime-provable'])` returns `environment-provable`\n    43→  - [x] 3.4: Confirm TIER_HIERARCHY ordering tests verify correct indices\n    44→  - [x] 3.5: Confirm LEGACY_TIER_MAP tests cover all four legacy entries\n    45→- [x] Task 4: Audit `verify-blackbox.test.ts` for tier-based enforcement (AC: 7, 8)\n    46→  - [x] 4.1: Confirm test-provable, runtime-provable skip Docker enforcement (blackBoxPass=true)\n    47→  - [x] 4.2: Confirm environment-provable runs Docker enforcement normally\n    48→  - [x] 4.3: Confirm escalate skips Docker enforcement\n    49→  - [x] 4.4: Confirm `**Tier:** unit-testable` backward compat skips Docker enforcement\n    50→  - [x] 4.5: Confirm `**Tier:** black-box` backward compat runs Docker enforcement\n    51→- [x] Task 5: Audit `validation-acs.test.ts` for new/deprecated function names (AC: 9)\n    52→  - [x] 5.1: Confirm `getTestProvableACs()` tests exist\n    53→  - [x] 5.2: Confirm `getCliVerifiableACs()` (deprecated alias) tests exist and return same data as `getTestProvableACs()`\n    54→  - [x] 5.3: Confirm `getEnvironmentProvableACs()` and `getIntegrationRequiredACs()` equivalence tests exist\n    55→- [x] Task 6: Audit `validation-runner.test.ts` for regressions (AC: 10)\n    56→  - [x] 6.1: Run the existing test file and confirm all tests pass\n    57→  - [x] 6.2: No behavioral changes expected — just verify no regressions\n    58→- [x] Task 7: Audit `verify-parser.test.ts` parseStoryACs tier field (AC: 11)\n    59→  - [x] 7.1: Confirm parseStoryACs test assertions include `tier` field on returned `ParsedAC` objects\n    60→  - [x] 7.2: Confirm both old-format tags and new-format tags produce correct `tier` values\n    61→- [x] Task 8: Run full test suite (AC: 12)\n    62→  - [x] 8.1: Run `npm test` and confirm 0 failures\n    63→  - [x] 8.2: Fix any regressions found during the audit tasks\n    64→\n    65→## Dev Notes\n    66→\n    67→This story is primarily an audit-and-fill-gaps story. Stories 16-1 through 16-7 each added tests for the tier changes they introduced. The purpose of 16-8 is to:\n    68→\n    69→1. **Systematically verify** all test files cover the new four-tier vocabulary\n    70→2. **Fill any gaps** where tests were missed during incremental development\n    71→3. **Confirm `npm test` passes** with zero regressions as a final gate\n    72→\n    73→### What Already Exists (from previous stories)\n    74→\n    75→Based on code inspection:\n    76→- `verify-parser.test.ts` already has `classifyTier` tests (all four tiers, priority order, case insensitivity), `parseVerificationTag` tests (all four new tiers, legacy backward compat for `cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`, `unit-testable`, `black-box`), and `parseStoryACs` tests with `tier` field assertions.\n    77→- `verification-tier.test.ts` already has `maxTier` tests (empty array, single tier, pairs, all four, order independence, duplicates), `TIER_HIERARCHY` ordering tests, and `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` tests.\n    78→- `verify-blackbox.test.ts` already has tier-based Docker enforcement tests for all four tiers plus `unit-testable` and `black-box` backward compat.\n    79→- `validation-acs.test.ts` already uses `getTestProvableACs()`, `getEnvironmentProvableACs()`, `getCliVerifiableACs()`, and `getIntegrationRequiredACs()` with equivalence checks.\n    80→\n    81→### Expected Outcome\n    82→\n    83→If all previous stories were implemented correctly, this story may require **zero code changes** — just verification that everything passes. Any gaps found should be filled with targeted test additions.\n    84→\n    85→### Key Constraints\n    86→\n    87→- **Do NOT break existing tests.** This is a verification gate, not a rewrite.\n    88→- **All ACs are test-provable.** Every AC can be verified by reading test files and running `npm test`.\n    89→- **Test files to inspect:**\n    90→  - `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts`\n    91→  - `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-tier.test.ts`\n    92→  - `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-blackbox.test.ts`\n    93→  - `src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-acs.test.ts`\n    94→  - `src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-runner.test.ts`\n    95→  - `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify.test.ts`\n    96→  - `src/modules/verify/__tests__/index.test.ts`\n    97→\n    98→### Context from Previous Stories\n    99→\n   100→- Story 16-1: Defined `VerificationTier` type, `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `maxTier()`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` in `types.ts`. Added `verification-tier.test.ts`.\n   101→- Story 16-2: Rewrote parser to use `classifyTier()`. Updated `verify-parser.test.ts`.\n   102→- Story 16-3: Updated proof validation for all four tier names. Updated `verify-blackbox.test.ts`.\n   103→- Story 16-4: Updated validation ACs and runner. Updated `validation-acs.test.ts`.\n   104→- Story 16-5: Rewrote harness-run verification dispatch. Added `harness-run-dispatch.test.ts`.\n   105→- Story 16-6: Updated create-story workflow. Added `create-story-tier-criteria.test.ts`.\n   106→- Story 16-7: Updated knowledge and enforcement docs. Added `verification-tier-docs.test.ts`.\n   107→\n   108→### References\n   109→\n   110→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md#Task 8] — \"Update all tests\"\n   111→- [Source: src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts] — classifyTier, parseVerificationTag, parseStoryACs tests\n   112→- [Source: src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-tier.test.ts] — maxTier, TIER_HIERARCHY, LEGACY_TIER_MAP tests\n   113→- [Source: src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-blackbox.test.ts] — Tier-based Docker enforcement tests\n   114→- [Source: src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-acs.test.ts] — New and deprecated function name tests\n   115→- [Source: src/modules/verify/types.ts#L14-L38] — `VerificationTier`, `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`\n   116→\n   117→## Files to Change\n   118→\n   119→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts` — Audit and fill gaps in `classifyTier`, `parseVerificationTag`, `parseStoryACs` tier coverage.\n   120→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-tier.test.ts` — Audit `maxTier`, `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` coverage.\n   121→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-blackbox.test.ts` — Audit tier-based Docker enforcement tests.\n   122→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-acs.test.ts` — Audit new/deprecated function name tests.\n   123→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-runner.test.ts` — Verify no regressions.\n   124→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify.test.ts` — Audit for any tier-related gaps.\n   125→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/index.test.ts` — Verify re-exports still match.\n   126→\n   127→## Dev Agent Record\n   128→\n   129→### Implementation Plan\n   130→\n   131→This is an audit-only story. All test coverage was already implemented by stories 16-1 through 16-7. The implementation plan is:\n   132→\n   133→1. Read each test file and verify coverage against ACs\n   134→2. Run the full test suite to confirm zero regressions\n   135→3. Mark all tasks complete if no gaps found\n   136→\n   137→### Debug Log\n   138→\n   139→No issues encountered. All test files already had complete coverage.\n   140→\n   141→### Completion Notes\n   142→\n   143→Zero code changes required. All 12 acceptance criteria were satisfied by existing test coverage from stories 16-1 through 16-7. Detailed audit findings:\n   144→\n   145→- **AC1**: `classifyTier` in `verify-parser.test.ts` has 14 tests covering all four tiers, priority order, case insensitivity, and multiple keyword variants.\n   146→- **AC2**: `parseVerificationTag` has explicit tests for `test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate` (lines 414-432).\n   147→- **AC3**: Backward compat tests cover `cli-verifiable` -> `test-provable` (line 398), `integration-required` -> `environment-provable` (line 402), `unit-testable` -> `test-provable` (line 435), `black-box` -> `environment-provable` (line 439).\n   148→- **AC4-6**: `maxTier` tests in `verification-tier.test.ts` cover empty array (line 33), pair (line 42), triple (line 45), plus 8 additional edge cases.\n   149→- **AC7**: `verify-blackbox.test.ts` has tier-based Docker enforcement tests for all four tiers (lines 481-585).\n   150→- **AC8**: `unit-testable` backward compat test at line 587, `black-box` at line 608.\n   151→- **AC9**: `validation-acs.test.ts` tests both `getTestProvableACs()` (line 152) and `getCliVerifiableACs()` (line 187) with equivalence check (line 166).\n   152→- **AC10**: All `validation-runner.test.ts` tests pass — 4015 total vitest tests pass.\n   153→- **AC11**: `parseStoryACs` tests assert `tier` field at multiple points (lines 106, 111, 229, 232, 253-259, 333-336, 357-360).\n   154→- **AC12**: `npx vitest run` — 152 test files, 4015 tests passed, 0 failures. 6 pre-existing BATS integration test failures (unrelated `all_tasks_complete` / `get_current_task` tests in ralph loop).\n   155→\n   156→## Senior Developer Review (AI)\n   157→\n   158→**Reviewer:** Code Review Workflow (adversarial)\n   159→**Date:** 2026-03-27\n   160→**Verdict:** APPROVED — all ACs verified, no HIGH/MEDIUM issues\n   161→\n   162→### AC Verification (all 12 IMPLEMENTED)\n   163→\n   164→| AC | Status | Evidence |\n   165→|----|--------|----------|\n   166→| AC1 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-parser.test.ts` lines 451-528: 14 classifyTier tests covering all four tiers |\n   167→| AC2 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-parser.test.ts` lines 414-428: all four new tier tag values tested |\n   168→| AC3 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-parser.test.ts` lines 398-440: cli-verifiable, integration-required, unit-testable, black-box backward compat |\n   169→| AC4 | IMPLEMENTED | `verification-tier.test.ts` line 42: maxTier pair returns runtime-provable |\n   170→| AC5 | IMPLEMENTED | `verification-tier.test.ts` line 33: maxTier([]) returns test-provable |\n   171→| AC6 | IMPLEMENTED | `verification-tier.test.ts` line 45: maxTier triple returns environment-provable |\n   172→| AC7 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-blackbox.test.ts` lines 481-585: all four tiers tested for Docker enforcement |\n   173→| AC8 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-blackbox.test.ts` lines 587-606: unit-testable backward compat skips Docker |\n   174→| AC9 | IMPLEMENTED | `validation-acs.test.ts` lines 152-200: getTestProvableACs + getCliVerifiableACs equivalence |\n   175→| AC10 | IMPLEMENTED | validation-runner.test.ts: all tests pass, no regressions |\n   176→| AC11 | IMPLEMENTED | `verify-parser.test.ts` lines 106, 111, 229, 232, 253-259, 333-336, 357-360: tier field assertions |\n   177→| AC12 | IMPLEMENTED | 152 test files, 4015 tests, 0 failures |\n   178→\n   179→### Git vs Story Discrepancies\n   180→\n   181→None. Story claims zero code changes; git confirms no source files were modified.\n   182→\n   183→### Coverage\n   184→\n   185→- Overall: 96.86% (target: 90%) — PASS\n   186→- Per-file floor: all 158 files above 80% — PASS\n   187→\n   188→### Findings\n   189→\n   190→**LOW-1: classifyTier barrel re-export not tested through index.ts**\n   191→`classifyTier` is re-exported from `src/modules/verify/index.ts` (line 64) but `index.test.ts` mocks `parser.js` entirely and never verifies the `classifyTier` re-export works through the barrel. The `verification-tier.test.ts` tests barrel re-exports for `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `maxTier`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` (lines 141-147) but not `classifyTier`. This is LOW because `classifyTier` is thoroughly tested via direct import in `verify-parser.test.ts`.\n   192→\n   193→**LOW-2: Story line references in Dev Agent Record may drift**\n   194→The completion notes reference specific line numbers (e.g., \"lines 414-432\") which will become stale if test files are edited. This is a documentation fragility, not a code issue.\n   195→\n   196→**LOW-3: No negative-path test for classifyTier with conflicting runtime + test keywords**\n   197→Tests cover escalate > environment > runtime priority, but don't test runtime > test priority explicitly (e.g., a description with both \"function returns\" and \"CLI output\" keywords). Currently covered implicitly by the priority-order test at line 501-506, but a dedicated test would be clearer.\n   198→\n   199→## File List\n   200→\n   201→No files changed. This was an audit-only story.\n   202→\n   203→## Change Log\n   204→\n   205→- 2026-03-27: Audit completed — all test coverage confirmed present from stories 16-1 through 16-7. Zero code changes needed. Story marked for review.\n   206→- 2026-03-27: Adversarial code review completed — all 12 ACs verified IMPLEMENTED, 0 HIGH/MEDIUM issues, 3 LOW findings (tech debt). Coverage 96.86% overall, all files above 80%. Status set to verifying.\n   207→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019LroBg6Ci8opzgtfxSaJPr","session_id":"4b69c0d8-c2d9-426d-9413-456ae301bb7e","uuid":"f6ec2f0f-0e33-45d8-9eb6-6db165380f0e","timestamp":"2026-03-28T14:03:00.273Z"}
